==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obsolescent
<hw>Ob`so*les"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>obsolescens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>obsolescere</ets>, to wear out gradually, to fall into disuse;
<ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>) + <ets>solere</ets> to use, be
wont.]</ety> <def>Going out of use; becoming obsolete; passing into
desuetude.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obsolete</ent>⟦br⟧
